{"snp2.14":{"snp2.14:0.1":{"pli":"Sutta Nipāta 2.14 ","eng":"Anthology of Discourses 2.14 ","html":"<article id='snp2.14'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li></ul>"},"snp2.14:0.2":{"pli":"Dhammikasutta ","eng":"With Dhammika ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"snp2.14:1.1":{"pli":"Evaṃ me sutaṃ—","eng":"So I have heard. ","html":"<p><span class='evam'>{}</span>"},"snp2.14:1.2":{"pli":"ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme. ","eng":"At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery. ","html":"{}"},"snp2.14:1.3":{"pli":"Atha kho dhammiko upāsako pañcahi upāsakasatehi saddhiṃ yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho dhammiko upāsako bhagavantaṃ gāthāhi ajjhabhāsi: ","eng":"Then the lay follower Dhammika, together with five hundred lay followers, went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and addressed him in verse: ","html":"{}</p>"},"snp2.14:2.1":{"pli":"“Pucchāmi taṃ gotama bhūripañña, ","eng":"“I ask you, Gotama, whose wisdom is vast: ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.14:2.2":{"pli":"Kathaṅkaro sāvako sādhu hoti; ","eng":"what does one do to become a good disciple, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.14:2.3":{"pli":"Yo vā agārā anagārameti, ","eng":"both one who has left the home, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.14:2.4":{"pli":"Agārino vā panupāsakāse. ","eng":"and the lay followers staying at home? ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp2.14:3.1":{"pli":"Tuvañhi lokassa sadevakassa, ","eng":"For you understand the course and destiny ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.14:3.2":{"pli":"Gatiṃ pajānāsi parāyaṇañca; ","eng":"of the world with all its gods. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.14:3.3":{"pli":"Na catthi tulyo nipuṇatthadassī, ","eng":"There is no equal to you who sees the subtle meaning, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.14:3.4":{"pli":"Tuvañhi buddhaṃ pavaraṃ vadanti. ","eng":"for you are the Buddha most excellent, they say. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp2.14:4.1":{"pli":"Sabbaṃ tuvaṃ ñāṇamavecca dhammaṃ, ","eng":"Having experienced all knowledge, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.14:4.2":{"pli":"Pakāsesi satte anukampamāno; ","eng":"you explain the teaching out of sympathy for beings. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.14:4.3":{"pli":"Vivaṭṭacchadosi samantacakkhu, ","eng":"All-seer, you have cast off the veil, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.14:4.4":{"pli":"Virocasi vimalo sabbaloke. ","eng":"and immaculate, you shine on the whole world. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp2.14:5.1":{"pli":"Āgañchi te santike nāgarājā, ","eng":"The dragon king Erāvaṇa, <j>hearing you called ‘Victor’, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>","comm":"At <a href='index.html?q=dn20#11.7'>DN 20:11.7</a> Erāvaṇa is clearly a dragon, but later tradition depicted him as a great elephant, the mount of Sakka. "},"snp2.14:5.2":{"pli":"Erāvaṇo nāma jinoti sutvā; ","eng":"came into your presence. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.14:5.3":{"pli":"Sopi tayā mantayitvājjhagamā, ","eng":"He consulted with you then, <j>having heard your words, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.14:5.4":{"pli":"Sādhūti sutvāna patītarūpo. ","eng":"left consoled, saying ‘Excellent!’ ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp2.14:6.1":{"pli":"Rājāpi taṃ vessavaṇo kuvero, ","eng":"And King Kuvera Vessavaṇa also ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>","comm":"Kuvera is identified as Vessavaṇa at <a href='index.html?q=dn32#7.43'>DN 32:7.43</a>. "},"snp2.14:6.2":{"pli":"Upeti dhammaṃ paripucchamāno; ","eng":"approached to ask about the teaching. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.14:6.3":{"pli":"Tassāpi tvaṃ pucchito brūsi dhīra, ","eng":"You also answered him, O attentive one, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.14:6.4":{"pli":"So cāpi sutvāna patītarūpo. ","eng":"and hearing you he too was consoled. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp2.14:7.1":{"pli":"Ye kecime titthiyā vādasīlā, ","eng":"Those monastics of other religions given to debate, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>","comm":"While <i lang='pi' translate='no'>titthiya</i> is commonly found in the Vinaya, this is the only place it occurs in the suttas that is not part of a stock list including kings, etc., or compounded with <i lang='pi' translate='no'>añña-</i> or <i lang='pi' translate='no'>nānā-</i>. "},"snp2.14:7.2":{"pli":"Ājīvakā vā yadi vā nigaṇṭhā; ","eng":"whether Ājīvakas or Jains, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.14:7.3":{"pli":"Paññāya taṃ nātitaranti sabbe, ","eng":"all fail to overtake you in wisdom, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.14:7.4":{"pli":"Ṭhito vajantaṃ viya sīghagāmiṃ. ","eng":"like a standing man next to a sprinter. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp2.14:8.1":{"pli":"Ye kecime brāhmaṇā vādasīlā, ","eng":"Those brahmins given to debate, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.14:8.2":{"pli":"Vuddhā cāpi brāhmaṇā santi keci; ","eng":"some of whom are quite senior, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.14:8.3":{"pli":"Sabbe tayi atthabaddhā bhavanti, ","eng":"all end up beholden to you for the meaning, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.14:8.4":{"pli":"Ye cāpi aññe vādino maññamānā. ","eng":"and others too who think themselves debaters. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp2.14:9.1":{"pli":"Ayañhi dhammo nipuṇo sukho ca, ","eng":"So subtle and pleasant is the teaching ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.14:9.2":{"pli":"Yoyaṃ tayā bhagavā suppavutto; ","eng":"that is well proclaimed by you, Blessed One. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.14:9.3":{"pli":"Tameva sabbepi sussūsamānā, ","eng":"It’s all we long to hear. So when asked, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.14:9.4":{"pli":"Taṃ no vada pucchito buddhaseṭṭha. ","eng":"O Best of Buddhas, tell us! ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp2.14:10.1":{"pli":"Sabbepime bhikkhavo sannisinnā, ","eng":"All these mendicants have gathered, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.14:10.2":{"pli":"Upāsakā cāpi tatheva sotuṃ; ","eng":"and the layfolk too are here to listen. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.14:10.3":{"pli":"Suṇantu dhammaṃ vimalenānubuddhaṃ, ","eng":"Let them hear the teaching <j>the immaculate one discovered, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.14:10.4":{"pli":"Subhāsitaṃ vāsavasseva devā”. ","eng":"like gods listening to the fine words of Vāsava.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp2.14:11.1":{"pli":"“Suṇātha me bhikkhavo sāvayāmi vo, ","eng":"“Listen to me, mendicants, I will educate you ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.14:11.2":{"pli":"Dhammaṃ dhutaṃ tañca carātha sabbe; ","eng":"in the cleansing teaching; all bear it in mind. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.14:11.3":{"pli":"Iriyāpathaṃ pabbajitānulomikaṃ, ","eng":"An intelligent person, seeing the meaning, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>","comm":"<i lang='pi' translate='no'>Atthadaso</i>: Bodhi follows comm in “seeing the good”, Norman has “seeing the goal”. I usually have “seeing the meaning”, and I think that is supported here. It follows several lines talking about the teaching. A reflective person doesn't just hear the teaching, but understands the point of it and puts it into practice. "},"snp2.14:11.4":{"pli":"Sevetha naṃ atthadaso mutīmā. ","eng":"would adopt the deportment <j>proper to a renunciate. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp2.14:12.1":{"pli":"No ve vikāle vicareyya bhikkhu, ","eng":"No way would a mendicant go out at the wrong time; ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.14:12.2":{"pli":"Gāme ca piṇḍāya careyya kāle; ","eng":"at the right time, they’d walk the village for alms. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.14:12.3":{"pli":"Akālacāriñhi sajanti saṅgā, ","eng":"For chains bind one who wanders at the wrong time, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.14:12.4":{"pli":"Tasmā vikāle na caranti buddhā. ","eng":"which is why the Buddhas avoid it. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp2.14:13.1":{"pli":"Rūpā ca saddā ca rasā ca gandhā, ","eng":"Sights, sounds, tastes, smells, and touches, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.14:13.2":{"pli":"Phassā ca ye sammadayanti satte; ","eng":"which drive beings mad—","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.14:13.3":{"pli":"Etesu dhammesu vineyya chandaṃ, ","eng":"dispel desire for such things, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.14:13.4":{"pli":"Kālena so pavise pātarāsaṃ. ","eng":"and enter for the morning meal at the right time. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp2.14:14.1":{"pli":"Piṇḍañca bhikkhu samayena laddhā, ","eng":"After receiving alms for the day, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.14:14.2":{"pli":"Eko paṭikkamma raho nisīde; ","eng":"on returning a mendicant would sit in private alone. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.14:14.3":{"pli":"Ajjhattacintī na mano bahiddhā, ","eng":"Inwardly reflective, they’d curb their mind ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.14:14.4":{"pli":"Nicchāraye saṅgahitattabhāvo. ","eng":"from outside things, keeping themselves collected. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp2.14:15.1":{"pli":"Sacepi so sallape sāvakena, ","eng":"Should they converse with a disciple, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.14:15.2":{"pli":"Aññena vā kenaci bhikkhunā vā; ","eng":"with anyone else, or with a mendicant, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.14:15.3":{"pli":"Dhammaṃ paṇītaṃ tamudāhareyya, ","eng":"they’d bring up only the sublime teaching, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.14:15.4":{"pli":"Na pesuṇaṃ nopi parūpavādaṃ. ","eng":"not dividing or blaming. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp2.14:16.1":{"pli":"Vādañhi eke paṭiseniyanti, ","eng":"For some contend in debate, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.14:16.2":{"pli":"Na te pasaṃsāma parittapaññe; ","eng":"but we praise not those of little wisdom. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.14:16.3":{"pli":"Tato tato ne pasajanti saṅgā, ","eng":"In place after place they are bound in chains, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.14:16.4":{"pli":"Cittañhi te tattha gamenti dūre. ","eng":"for they send their mind over there far away. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp2.14:17.1":{"pli":"Piṇḍaṃ vihāraṃ sayanāsanañca, ","eng":"Alms, a dwelling, a bed and seat, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.14:17.2":{"pli":"Āpañca saṅghāṭirajūpavāhanaṃ; ","eng":"and water for rinsing the dust from the cloak—","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.14:17.3":{"pli":"Sutvāna dhammaṃ sugatena desitaṃ, ","eng":"after hearing the teaching of the Holy One, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.14:17.4":{"pli":"Saṅkhāya seve varapaññasāvako. ","eng":"a disciple of outstanding wisdom would use these after appraisal. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp2.14:18.1":{"pli":"Tasmā hi piṇḍe sayanāsane ca, ","eng":"That’s why, when it comes to alms and lodgings, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.14:18.2":{"pli":"Āpe ca saṅghāṭirajūpavāhane; ","eng":"and water for rinsing the dust from the cloak, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.14:18.3":{"pli":"Etesu dhammesu anūpalitto, ","eng":"a mendicant is unsullied in the midst of these things, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.14:18.4":{"pli":"Bhikkhu yathā pokkhare vāribindu. ","eng":"like a droplet on a lotus-leaf. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp2.14:19.1":{"pli":"Gahaṭṭhavattaṃ pana vo vadāmi, ","eng":"Now I shall tell you the householder’s duty, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.14:19.2":{"pli":"Yathākaro sāvako sādhu hoti; ","eng":"doing which one becomes a good disciple. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.14:19.3":{"pli":"Na hesa labbhā sapariggahena, ","eng":"For one burdened with possessions <j>does not get to realize ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.14:19.4":{"pli":"Phassetuṃ yo kevalo bhikkhudhammo. ","eng":"the whole of the mendicant’s practice. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp2.14:20.1":{"pli":"Pāṇaṃ na hane na ca ghātayeyya, ","eng":"They’d not kill any creature, nor have them killed, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.14:20.2":{"pli":"Na cānujaññā hanataṃ paresaṃ; ","eng":"nor grant permission for others to kill. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.14:20.3":{"pli":"Sabbesu bhūtesu nidhāya daṇḍaṃ, ","eng":"They’ve laid aside violence towards all creatures ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.14:20.4":{"pli":"Ye thāvarā ye ca tasā santi loke. ","eng":"frail or firm that there are in the world. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp2.14:21.1":{"pli":"Tato adinnaṃ parivajjayeyya, ","eng":"Next, a disciple would avoid knowingly ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.14:21.2":{"pli":"Kiñci kvaci sāvako bujjhamāno; ","eng":"taking anything not given at all, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.14:21.3":{"pli":"Na hāraye harataṃ nānujaññā, ","eng":"they’d not get others to do it, <j>nor grant them permission to steal; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.14:21.4":{"pli":"Sabbaṃ adinnaṃ parivajjayeyya. ","eng":"they’d avoid <em>all</em> theft. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp2.14:22.1":{"pli":"Abrahmacariyaṃ parivajjayeyya, ","eng":"A sensible person would avoid the unchaste life, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.14:22.2":{"pli":"Aṅgārakāsuṃ jalitaṃva viññū; ","eng":"like a burning pit of coals. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.14:22.3":{"pli":"Asambhuṇanto pana brahmacariyaṃ, ","eng":"But if unable to remain chaste, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.14:22.4":{"pli":"Parassa dāraṃ na atikkameyya. ","eng":"they’d not transgress with another’s partner. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp2.14:23.1":{"pli":"Sabhaggato vā parisaggato vā, ","eng":"In a council or assembly, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.14:23.2":{"pli":"Ekassa veko na musā bhaṇeyya; ","eng":"or one on one, they would not lie. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.14:23.3":{"pli":"Na bhāṇaye bhaṇataṃ nānujaññā, ","eng":"They’d not get others to lie, <j>nor grant them permission to lie; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.14:23.4":{"pli":"Sabbaṃ abhūtaṃ parivajjayeyya. ","eng":"they’d avoid <em>all</em> untruths. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp2.14:24.1":{"pli":"Majjañca pānaṃ na samācareyya, ","eng":"A householder espousing this teaching ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.14:24.2":{"pli":"Dhammaṃ imaṃ rocaye yo gahaṭṭho; ","eng":"would not consume liquor or drink. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.14:24.3":{"pli":"Na pāyaye pivataṃ nānujaññā, ","eng":"They’d not get others to drink, <j>nor grant them permission to drink; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.14:24.4":{"pli":"Ummādanantaṃ iti naṃ viditvā. ","eng":"knowing that ends in intoxication. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp2.14:25.1":{"pli":"Madā hi pāpāni karonti bālā, ","eng":"For drunken fools do bad things, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.14:25.2":{"pli":"Kārenti caññepi jane pamatte; ","eng":"and encourage other heedless folk. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.14:25.3":{"pli":"Etaṃ apuññāyatanaṃ vivajjaye, ","eng":"Shun this field of demerit, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.14:25.4":{"pli":"Ummādanaṃ mohanaṃ bālakantaṃ. ","eng":"the maddening, deluding frolic of fools. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp2.14:26.1":{"pli":"Pāṇaṃ na hane na cādinnamādiye, ","eng":"You shouldn’t kill living creatures, or steal, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.14:26.2":{"pli":"Musā na bhāse na ca majjapo siyā; ","eng":"or lie, or drink liquor. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.14:26.3":{"pli":"Abrahmacariyā virameyya methunā, ","eng":"Be chaste, refraining from sex, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.14:26.4":{"pli":"Rattiṃ na bhuñjeyya vikālabhojanaṃ. ","eng":"and don’t eat at night, the wrong time. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp2.14:27.1":{"pli":"Mālaṃ na dhāre na ca gandhamācare, ","eng":"Not wearing garlands or applying fragrance, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.14:27.2":{"pli":"Mañce chamāyaṃ va sayetha santhate; ","eng":"you should sleep on a low bed, <j>or a mat on the ground. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.14:27.3":{"pli":"Etañhi aṭṭhaṅgikamāhuposathaṃ, ","eng":"This is the eight-factored sabbath, they say, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.14:27.4":{"pli":"Buddhena dukkhantagunā pakāsitaṃ. ","eng":"explained by the Buddha, <j>who has gone to suffering’s end. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp2.14:28.1":{"pli":"Tato ca pakkhassupavassuposathaṃ, ","eng":"Then having rightly undertaken the sabbath ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.14:28.2":{"pli":"Cātuddasiṃ pañcadasiñca aṭṭhamiṃ; ","eng":"complete in all its eight factors ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.14:28.3":{"pli":"Pāṭihāriyapakkhañca pasannamānaso, ","eng":"on the fourteenth, fifteenth, <j>and eighth of the fortnight, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.14:28.4":{"pli":"Aṭṭhaṅgupetaṃ susamattarūpaṃ. ","eng":"as well as on the fortnightly special displays, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp2.14:29.1":{"pli":"Tato ca pāto upavutthuposatho, ","eng":"at daybreak after the sabbath ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.14:29.2":{"pli":"Annena pānena ca bhikkhusaṅghaṃ; ","eng":"a clever person, rejoicing with confident heart, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.14:29.3":{"pli":"Pasannacitto anumodamāno, ","eng":"would distribute food and drink ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.14:29.4":{"pli":"Yathārahaṃ saṃvibhajetha viññū. ","eng":"to the mendicant Saṅgha as is fitting. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp2.14:30.1":{"pli":"Dhammena mātāpitaro bhareyya, ","eng":"One should rightfully support one’s parents, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.14:30.2":{"pli":"Payojaye dhammikaṃ so vaṇijjaṃ; ","eng":"and undertake a legitimate business. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.14:30.3":{"pli":"Etaṃ gihī vattayamappamatto, ","eng":"A diligent layperson observing these duties ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.14:30.4":{"pli":"Sayampabhe nāma upeti deve”ti. ","eng":"ascends to the gods called Self-luminous.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote>"},"snp2.14:30.5":{"pli":"Dhammikasuttaṃ cuddasamaṃ. ","html":"<p class='endsutta'>{}</p>"},"snp2.14:30.6":{"pli":"Cūḷavaggo dutiyo. ","html":"<p class='endvagga'>{}</p>"},"snp2.14:31.0":{"pli":"Tassuddānaṃ ","html":"<p class='uddana-intro'>{}</p>"},"snp2.14:31.1":{"pli":"Ratanāmagandho hiri ca, ","html":"<blockquote class='uddanagatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.14:31.2":{"pli":"maṅgalaṃ sūcilomena; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.14:31.3":{"pli":"Dhammacariyañca brāhmaṇo, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.14:31.4":{"pli":"nāvā kiṃsīlamuṭṭhānaṃ. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp2.14:32.1":{"pli":"Rāhulo puna kappo ca, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.14:32.2":{"pli":"paribbājaniyaṃ tathā; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.14:32.3":{"pli":"Dhammikañca viduno āhu, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.14:32.4":{"pli":"cūḷavagganti cuddasāti. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote></article>"}},"snp2.2":{"snp2.2:0.1":{"pli":"Sutta Nipāta 2.2 ","eng":"Anthology of Discourses 2.2 ","html":"<article id='snp2.2'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li></ul>"},"snp2.2:0.2":{"pli":"Āmagandhasutta ","eng":"Putrefaction ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"snp2.2:1.1":{"pli":"“Sāmākaciṅgūlakacīnakāni ca, ","eng":"“The good eat properly obtained ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.2:1.2":{"pli":"Pattapphalaṃ mūlaphalaṃ gavipphalaṃ; ","eng":"millet, wild grains, broomcorn, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.2:1.3":{"pli":"Dhammena laddhaṃ satamasnamānā, ","eng":"greens, tubers, and squashes. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.2:1.4":{"pli":"Na kāmakāmā alikaṃ bhaṇanti. ","eng":"They don’t lie to get what they want. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp2.2:2.1":{"pli":"Yadasnamāno sukataṃ suniṭṭhitaṃ, ","eng":"But when you eat delicious food, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.2:2.2":{"pli":"Parehi dinnaṃ payataṃ paṇītaṃ; ","eng":"nicely cooked and prepared, and offered by others, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>","comm":"<i lang='pi' translate='no'>Dinnaṁ</i> and <i lang='pi' translate='no'>payataṁ</i> are synonyms. "},"snp2.2:2.3":{"pli":"Sālīnamannaṃ paribhuñjamāno, ","eng":"enjoying a dish of fine rice, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.2:2.4":{"pli":"So bhuñjasī kassapa āmagandhaṃ. ","eng":"Kassapa, you eat putrefaction. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>","comm":"“Putrefaction” (<i lang='pi' translate='no'>āmagandha</i>) was to be shunned by Jain ascetics (Ācaraṅgasūtra 1.5.1.10.15: <i lang='pi' translate='no'>savv’ āmagandhaṁ parinnāya nirāmagandhe parivvae</i>.) "},"snp2.2:3.1":{"pli":"Na āmagandho mama kappatīti, ","eng":"‘Putrefaction is not appropriate for me’—","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.2:3.2":{"pli":"Icceva tvaṃ bhāsasi brahmabandhu; ","eng":"so you said, O brahmin only by kin. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.2:3.3":{"pli":"Sālīnamannaṃ paribhuñjamāno, ","eng":"Yet here you are enjoying a dish of fine rice, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.2:3.4":{"pli":"Sakuntamaṃsehi susaṅkhatehi; ","eng":"nicely cooked with the flesh of fowl. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.2:3.5":{"pli":"Pucchāmi taṃ kassapa etamatthaṃ, ","eng":"I’m asking you this, Kassapa: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.2:3.6":{"pli":"Kathaṃpakāro tava āmagandho”. ","eng":"what do you take to be putrefaction?” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp2.2:4.1":{"pli":"“Pāṇātipāto vadhachedabandhanaṃ, ","eng":"“Killing creatures, mutilation, murder, abduction; ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.2:4.2":{"pli":"Theyyaṃ musāvādo nikativañcanāni ca; ","eng":"stealing, lying, cheating and fraud, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.2:4.3":{"pli":"Ajjhenakuttaṃ paradārasevanā, ","eng":"learning crooked spells, adultery: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>","comm":"Read <i lang='pi' translate='no'>kujja</i>. "},"snp2.2:4.4":{"pli":"Esāmagandho na hi maṃsabhojanaṃ. ","eng":"this is putrefaction, not eating meat. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp2.2:5.1":{"pli":"Ye idha kāmesu asaññatā janā, ","eng":"People here with unbridled sensuality, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.2:5.2":{"pli":"Rasesu giddhā asucibhāvamassitā; ","eng":"greedy for tastes, mixed up in impurity, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.2:5.3":{"pli":"Natthikadiṭṭhī visamā durannayā, ","eng":"nihilists, immoral, intractable: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.2:5.4":{"pli":"Esāmagandho na hi maṃsabhojanaṃ. ","eng":"this is putrefaction, not eating meat. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp2.2:6.1":{"pli":"Ye lūkhasā dāruṇā piṭṭhimaṃsikā, ","eng":"Tough, callous backbiters, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.2:6.2":{"pli":"Mittadduno nikkaruṇātimānino; ","eng":"pitiless and arrogant betrayers of friends, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.2:6.3":{"pli":"Adānasīlā na ca denti kassaci, ","eng":"misers who never give anything: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.2:6.4":{"pli":"Esāmagandho na hi maṃsabhojanaṃ. ","eng":"this is putrefaction, not eating meat. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp2.2:7.1":{"pli":"Kodho mado thambho paccupaṭṭhāpanā, ","eng":"Anger, vanity, obstinacy, contrariness, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.2:7.2":{"pli":"Māyā usūyā bhassasamussayo ca; ","eng":"deceit, jealousy, boastfulness, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.2:7.3":{"pli":"Mānātimāno ca asabbhi santhavo, ","eng":"haughtiness, intimacy with the wicked: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>","comm":"Here <i lang='pi' translate='no'>asabbhi</i> is instrumental of <i lang='pi' translate='no'>asanta</i>, “wicked person”. "},"snp2.2:7.4":{"pli":"Esāmagandho na hi maṃsabhojanaṃ. ","eng":"this is putrefaction, not eating meat. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp2.2:8.1":{"pli":"Ye pāpasīlā iṇaghātasūcakā, ","eng":"The ill-behaved, debt-evaders, slanderers, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.2:8.2":{"pli":"Vohārakūṭā idha pāṭirūpikā; ","eng":"business cheats and con-artists, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.2:8.3":{"pli":"Narādhamā yedha karonti kibbisaṃ, ","eng":"vile men committing sin: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.2:8.4":{"pli":"Esāmagandho na hi maṃsabhojanaṃ. ","eng":"this is putrefaction, not eating meat. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp2.2:9.1":{"pli":"Ye idha pāṇesu asaññatā janā, ","eng":"People here who can’t stop harming living creatures, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.2:9.2":{"pli":"Paresamādāya vihesamuyyutā; ","eng":"taking from others, intent on hurting, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.2:9.3":{"pli":"Dussīlaluddā pharusā anādarā, ","eng":"immoral, cruel, harsh, lacking regard for others: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.2:9.4":{"pli":"Esāmagandho na hi maṃsabhojanaṃ. ","eng":"this is putrefaction, not eating meat. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp2.2:10.1":{"pli":"Etesu giddhā viruddhātipātino, ","eng":"Greedy, hostile, aggressive to others, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.2:10.2":{"pli":"Niccuyyutā pecca tamaṃ vajanti ye; ","eng":"and addicted to evil—<j>those beings pass into darkness, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.2:10.3":{"pli":"Patanti sattā nirayaṃ avaṃsirā, ","eng":"falling headlong into hell: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.2:10.4":{"pli":"Esāmagandho na hi maṃsabhojanaṃ. ","eng":"this is putrefaction, not eating meat. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp2.2:11.1":{"pli":"Na macchamaṃsānamanāsakattaṃ, ","eng":"Not fish or flesh or fasting, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.2:11.2":{"pli":"Na naggiyaṃ na muṇḍiyaṃ jaṭājallaṃ; ","eng":"nudity or baldness, or dreadlocks or dirt, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.2:11.3":{"pli":"Kharājināni nāggihuttassupasevanā, ","eng":"not rough hides or serving the sacred flame, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.2:11.4":{"pli":"Ye vāpi loke amarā bahū tapā; ","eng":"or the many endless mortifications in the world, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>","comm":"The split compound <i lang='pi' translate='no'>amaraṁ tapaṁ</i> occurs at <a href='index.html?q=sn4.1#5.2'>SN 4.1:5.2</a> and <a href='index.html?q=thag3.1#1.4'>Thag 3.1:1.4</a>, while here we have <i lang='pi' translate='no'>amarā bahū tapā</i>. The commentary explains that <i lang='pi' translate='no'>amara</i> here is “immortality”, and the phrase means “fervent mortification aimed at immortality”. However, I find this unconvincing, one reason being that <i lang='pi' translate='no'>amara</i> is an adjective (and thus must be glossed with an abstract noun in dative, <i lang='pi' translate='no'>amarabhāvatthāya</i>). It is simpler to assume Pali has an idiomatic sense of <i lang='pi' translate='no'>amara</i> as “endless”, which occurs here, in the phrase <i lang='pi' translate='no'>amarāvikkhepa</i> (<a href='index.html?q=dn1#2.23.1'>DN 1:2.23.1</a>), and in the Niddesa’s <i lang='pi' translate='no'>amarāvitakka</i> (<a href='index.html?q=cnd12#6.1'>Cnd 12:6.1</a>). Then <i lang='pi' translate='no'>amarā</i> and <i lang='pi' translate='no'>bahū</i> are synonyms. I cannot find any use in Sanskrit that parallels this, but <i lang='pi' translate='no'>amara</i> is noted by Edgerton in Buddhist Hybrid Sanskrit as “a high number”. "},"snp2.2:11.5":{"pli":"Mantāhutī yaññamutūpasevanā, ","eng":"not hymns or oblations, <j>sacrifices or seasonal observances, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.2:11.6":{"pli":"Sodhenti maccaṃ avitiṇṇakaṅkhaṃ. ","eng":"will cleanse a mortal not free of doubt. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp2.2:12.1":{"pli":"Sotesu gutto viditindriyo care, ","eng":"Guarding the streams of sense impressions, <j>wander with faculties conquered, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.2:12.2":{"pli":"Dhamme ṭhito ajjavamaddave rato; ","eng":"standing on the teaching, delighting in sincerity and tenderness. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.2:12.3":{"pli":"Saṅgātigo sabbadukkhappahīno, ","eng":"The wise have slipped their chains <j>and given up all suffering; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.2:12.4":{"pli":"Na lippati diṭṭhasutesu dhīro”. ","eng":"they don’t cling to the seen and the heard.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp2.2:13.1":{"pli":"Iccetamatthaṃ bhagavā punappunaṃ, ","eng":"The Buddha explained this matter to him <j>again and again, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>","comm":"The concluding verses identify the “Kassapa” of the poem as the Buddha Kassapa of the past. The commentary says this was added at the Council. "},"snp2.2:13.2":{"pli":"Akkhāsi naṃ vedayi mantapāragū; ","eng":"until the master of hymns understood it. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.2:13.3":{"pli":"Citrāhi gāthāhi munī pakāsayi, ","eng":"It was illustrated with colorful verses ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.2:13.4":{"pli":"Nirāmagandho asito durannayo. ","eng":"by the sage free of putrefaction, <j>unattached, hard to trace. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp2.2:14.1":{"pli":"Sutvāna buddhassa subhāsitaṃ padaṃ, ","eng":"Having heard the fine words of the Buddha, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.2:14.2":{"pli":"Nirāmagandhaṃ sabbadukkhappanūdanaṃ; ","eng":"that are free of putrefaction, <j>casting aside all suffering; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.2:14.3":{"pli":"Nīcamano vandi tathāgatassa, ","eng":"humbled, he bowed to the Realized One, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.2:14.4":{"pli":"Tattheva pabbajjamarocayitthāti. ","eng":"and right away begged to go forth. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote>"},"snp2.2:14.5":{"pli":"Āmagandhasuttaṃ dutiyaṃ. ","html":"<p class='endsutta'>{}</p></article>"}},"snp2.3":{"snp2.3:0.1":{"pli":"Sutta Nipāta 2.3 ","eng":"Anthology of Discourses 2.3 ","html":"<article id='snp2.3'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li></ul>"},"snp2.3:0.2":{"pli":"Hirisutta ","eng":"Conscientious Companionship ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"snp2.3:1.1":{"pli":"Hiriṃ tarantaṃ vijigucchamānaṃ, ","eng":"Flouting conscience, loathing it, ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.3:1.2":{"pli":"Tavāhamasmi iti bhāsamānaṃ; ","eng":"saying “I’m on your side”, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.3:1.3":{"pli":"Sayhāni kammāni anādiyantaṃ, ","eng":"but not following up in deeds—","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.3:1.4":{"pli":"Neso mamanti iti naṃ vijaññā. ","eng":"know they’re not on your side. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp2.3:2.1":{"pli":"Ananvayaṃ piyaṃ vācaṃ, ","eng":"Some say nice things to their friends ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.3:2.2":{"pli":"yo mittesu pakubbati; ","eng":"without following it up. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.3:2.3":{"pli":"Akarontaṃ bhāsamānaṃ, ","eng":"The wise will recognize ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.3:2.4":{"pli":"parijānanti paṇḍitā. ","eng":"one who talks without doing. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp2.3:3.1":{"pli":"Na so mitto yo sadā appamatto, ","eng":"No true friend relentlessly ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.3:3.2":{"pli":"Bhedāsaṅkī randhamevānupassī; ","eng":"suspects betrayal, looking for fault. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.3:3.3":{"pli":"Yasmiñca seti urasīva putto, ","eng":"One on whom you rest, like a child on the breast, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.3:3.4":{"pli":"Sa ve mitto yo parehi abhejjo. ","eng":"is a true friend, not split from you by others. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp2.3:4.1":{"pli":"Pāmujjakaraṇaṃ ṭhānaṃ, ","eng":"One whose reward is the fruit ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.3:4.2":{"pli":"pasaṃsāvahanaṃ sukhaṃ; ","eng":"of bearing the burden of service ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.3:4.3":{"pli":"Phalānisaṃso bhāveti, ","eng":"develops a happy state, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.3:4.4":{"pli":"vahanto porisaṃ dhuraṃ. ","eng":"producing joy and attracting praise. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp2.3:5.1":{"pli":"Pavivekarasaṃ pitvā, ","eng":"One who has drunk the nectar of seclusion ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.3:5.2":{"pli":"Rasaṃ upasamassa ca; ","eng":"and the nectar of peace, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.3:5.3":{"pli":"Niddaro hoti nippāpo, ","eng":"free of stress, free of evil, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.3:5.4":{"pli":"Dhammapītirasaṃ pivanti. ","eng":"drinks the joyous nectar of Dhamma. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote>"},"snp2.3:5.5":{"pli":"Hirisuttaṃ tatiyaṃ. ","html":"<p class='endsutta'>{}</p></article>"}},"snp2.4":{"snp2.4:0.1":{"pli":"Sutta Nipāta 2.4 ","eng":"Anthology of Discourses 2.4 ","html":"<article id='snp2.4'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li></ul>"},"snp2.4:0.2":{"pli":"Maṅgalasutta ","eng":"Blessings ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"snp2.4:1.1":{"pli":"Evaṃ me sutaṃ—","eng":"So I have heard. ","html":"<p><span class='evam'>{}</span>"},"snp2.4:1.2":{"pli":"ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme. ","eng":"At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery. ","html":"{}"},"snp2.4:1.3":{"pli":"Atha kho aññatarā devatā abhikkantāya rattiyā abhikkantavaṇṇā kevalakappaṃ jetavanaṃ obhāsetvā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi. ","eng":"Then, late at night, a glorious deity, lighting up the entire Jeta’s Grove, went up to the Buddha, bowed, and stood to one side. ","html":"{}"},"snp2.4:1.4":{"pli":"Ekamantaṃ ṭhitā kho sā devatā bhagavantaṃ gāthāya ajjhabhāsi: ","eng":"Standing to one side, that deity addressed the Buddha in verse: ","html":"{}</p>"},"snp2.4:2.1":{"pli":"“Bahū devā manussā ca, ","eng":"“Many gods and humans ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.4:2.2":{"pli":"maṅgalāni acintayuṃ; ","eng":"have thought about blessings ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.4:2.3":{"pli":"Ākaṅkhamānā sotthānaṃ, ","eng":"desiring well-being: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.4:2.4":{"pli":"brūhi maṅgalamuttamaṃ”. ","eng":"declare the highest blessing.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp2.4:3.1":{"pli":"“Asevanā ca bālānaṃ, ","eng":"“Not to fraternize with fools, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.4:3.2":{"pli":"paṇḍitānañca sevanā; ","eng":"but to fraternize with the wise, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.4:3.3":{"pli":"Pūjā ca pūjaneyyānaṃ, ","eng":"and honoring those worthy of honor: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.4:3.4":{"pli":"etaṃ maṅgalamuttamaṃ. ","eng":"this is the highest blessing. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp2.4:4.1":{"pli":"Patirūpadesavāso ca, ","eng":"Living in a suitable region, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.4:4.2":{"pli":"pubbe ca katapuññatā; ","eng":"having made merit in the past, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.4:4.3":{"pli":"Attasammāpaṇidhi ca, ","eng":"being rightly resolved in oneself, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.4:4.4":{"pli":"etaṃ maṅgalamuttamaṃ. ","eng":"this is the highest blessing. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp2.4:5.1":{"pli":"Bāhusaccañca sippañca, ","eng":"Education and a craft, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.4:5.2":{"pli":"vinayo ca susikkhito; ","eng":"discipline and training, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.4:5.3":{"pli":"Subhāsitā ca yā vācā, ","eng":"and well-spoken speech: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.4:5.4":{"pli":"etaṃ maṅgalamuttamaṃ. ","eng":"this is the highest blessing. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp2.4:6.1":{"pli":"Mātāpitu upaṭṭhānaṃ, ","eng":"Caring for mother and father, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.4:6.2":{"pli":"puttadārassa saṅgaho; ","eng":"kindness to children and partners, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.4:6.3":{"pli":"Anākulā ca kammantā, ","eng":"and unstressful work: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.4:6.4":{"pli":"etaṃ maṅgalamuttamaṃ. ","eng":"this is the highest blessing. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp2.4:7.1":{"pli":"Dānañca dhammacariyā ca, ","eng":"Giving and righteous conduct, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.4:7.2":{"pli":"ñātakānañca saṅgaho; ","eng":"kindness to relatives, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.4:7.3":{"pli":"Anavajjāni kammāni, ","eng":"blameless deeds: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.4:7.4":{"pli":"etaṃ maṅgalamuttamaṃ. ","eng":"this is the highest blessing. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp2.4:8.1":{"pli":"Āratī viratī pāpā, ","eng":"Desisting and abstaining from evil, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.4:8.2":{"pli":"majjapānā ca saṃyamo; ","eng":"avoiding drinking liquor, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.4:8.3":{"pli":"Appamādo ca dhammesu, ","eng":"diligence in good qualities: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.4:8.4":{"pli":"etaṃ maṅgalamuttamaṃ. ","eng":"this is the highest blessing. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp2.4:9.1":{"pli":"Gāravo ca nivāto ca, ","eng":"Respect and humility, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.4:9.2":{"pli":"santuṭṭhi ca kataññutā; ","eng":"contentment and gratitude, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.4:9.3":{"pli":"Kālena dhammassavanaṃ, ","eng":"and timely listening to the teaching: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.4:9.4":{"pli":"etaṃ maṅgalamuttamaṃ. ","eng":"this is the highest blessing. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp2.4:10.1":{"pli":"Khantī ca sovacassatā, ","eng":"Patience, being easy to admonish, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.4:10.2":{"pli":"samaṇānañca dassanaṃ; ","eng":"the sight of ascetics, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.4:10.3":{"pli":"Kālena dhammasākacchā, ","eng":"and timely discussion of the teaching: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.4:10.4":{"pli":"etaṃ maṅgalamuttamaṃ. ","eng":"this is the highest blessing. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp2.4:11.1":{"pli":"Tapo ca brahmacariyañca, ","eng":"Fervor and chastity ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.4:11.2":{"pli":"Ariyasaccāna dassanaṃ; ","eng":"seeing the noble truths, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.4:11.3":{"pli":"Nibbānasacchikiriyā ca, ","eng":"and realization of extinguishment: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.4:11.4":{"pli":"Etaṃ maṅgalamuttamaṃ. ","eng":"this is the highest blessing. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp2.4:12.1":{"pli":"Phuṭṭhassa lokadhammehi, ","eng":"Though touched by worldly things, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.4:12.2":{"pli":"Cittaṃ yassa na kampati; ","eng":"their mind does not tremble; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.4:12.3":{"pli":"Asokaṃ virajaṃ khemaṃ, ","eng":"sorrowless, stainless, secure, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.4:12.4":{"pli":"Etaṃ maṅgalamuttamaṃ. ","eng":"this is the highest blessing. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp2.4:13.1":{"pli":"Etādisāni katvāna, ","eng":"Having completed these things, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.4:13.2":{"pli":"Sabbattha maparājitā; ","eng":"undefeated everywhere; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.4:13.3":{"pli":"Sabbattha sotthiṃ gacchanti, ","eng":"everywhere they go in safety: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp2.4:13.4":{"pli":"Taṃ tesaṃ maṅgalamuttaman”ti. ","eng":"this is their highest blessing.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote>"},"snp2.4:13.5":{"pli":"Maṅgalasuttaṃ catutthaṃ. ","html":"<p class='endsutta'>{}</p></article>"}}}